data.name: IncentiveCompletedAttestionText
data.value: Compass and your employer value your health and would like to encourage everyone to stay up to date with wellness exams and other important health activities. In some circumstances, your procedures may not have been captured in the claims data received by Compass. This submission will serve as a self-attestation of the completion of a requirement. This attestation is applicable to the active period of your employer's existing incentive program. As such, this attestation is not indefinite and may require an update at a future time. In addition, this submission gives Compass permission to perform audits to verify the accuracy of the information provided. By providing this information, you confirm that you understand that if you falsify any information, you may forfeit access to preferred plans, savings, incentives and health fund contributions, and may face other disciplinary actions based on your employee code of conduct.

data.name: IncentiveCantCompleteAttestationText
data.value: Compass and your employer value your health and would like to encourage everyone to stay up to date with wellness exams and other important health activities. In some circumstances, you may request to be exempt from completing an activity. This submission will serve as a formal request to be exempt for the completion of a requirement. This exemption is applicable to the active period of your employer's existing incentive program. As such, this exemption is not indefinite and may require an update at a future time. In addition, this submission gives Compass permission to perform audits to verify the accuracy of the information provided. By providing this information, you confirm that you understand that if you falsify any information, you may forfeit access to preferred plans, savings, incentives and health fund contributions, and may face other disciplinary actions based on your employee code of conduct.

data.name: BloodPressureDefiniton
data.value: Blood pressure is the pressure of the blood in the circulatory system. It is measured as systolic over diastolic.

data.name: HdlCholesterolDefiniton
data.value: HDL cholesterol is the well-behaved "good cholesterol." This friendly scavenger cruises the bloodstream. As it does, it removes harmful bad cholesterol from where it doesn't belong.

data.name: GlucoseDefiniton
data.value: A blood glucose test measures the amount of a type of sugar, called glucose, in your blood. Glucose comes from carbohydrate foods. It is the main source of energy used by the body.

data.name: TriglyceridesDefiniton
data.value: Triglycerides are a type of fat (lipid) found in your blood. When you eat, your body converts any calories it doesn't need to use right away into triglycerides.

data.name: WaistCirumferenceDefinition
data.value: Your waist size is a clue to whether you're at high risk for type 2 diabetes, high blood pressure, high cholesterol, and heart disease.
